        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued July 15 at 1:04AM CDT until July 15 at 1:30AM CDT by NWS Grand Forks ND</headline>
        <description>At 104 AM CDT, a severe thunderstorm was located near Hoople, or 14
miles northwest of Grafton, moving east at 40 mph.

HAZARD...Two inch hail and 60 mph wind gusts.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...People and animals outdoors will be injured. Expect hail
damage to roofs, siding, windows, and vehicles. Expect wind
damage to roofs, siding, and trees.

Locations impacted include...
Grafton, Park River, St. Thomas, Hoople, Edinburg, Crystal, and
Auburn.
</description>
        <instruction>This storm is producing large hail. SEEK SHELTER NOW inside a sturdy
structure and stay away from windows.</instruction>
